  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Mansi Brar Fernandes versus Shubha Sharma and Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_10_169_211','2025INSC1110'); ><font size='4'> <strong>MANSI BRAR FERNANDES<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>SHUBHA SHARMA AND ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 10 S.C.R. 169</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1110</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004132025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the appellants, fall within the category of &ldquo;speculative investors&rdquo; so as to disentitle them from initiating proceedings u/s.7 of the IBC; whether the Ordinance/Amendment Act introducing threshold requirements for filing of s.7 IBC applications by the present case. Headnotes&dagger; Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 &ndash; s.7 &ndash; NCLAT set aside the NCLT&rsquo;s order and reversed the admission of the application filed u/s.7 by the appellants, holding that they were &ldquo;speculative investors&rdquo; and not genuine homebuyers/<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 12-09-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 3826/2020</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_10_169_211','2025INSC1110','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><